 Ngqamakhwe police arrested three men, two aged 25 and the other aged 20, for alleged business robbery. "The trio was chased and caught by the police after they allegedly robbed a local shop at Esikolweni Location, Lambatha Village, Ngqamakhwe, on Friday, at about 14:00," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "Police recovered robbed items from the suspects. "All the three will now appear before the Ngqamakhwe Magistrate's Court on Monday on charges of business robbery." 